General.Name: Red Branch Technologies Inc
General.Description: Red Branch Technologies, Inc., a technology holding company, engages in the development and commercialization of security and defense industry solutions. It offers The Mini that supports a combination of applications, such as mesh networks; The Mojo, which supports various applications, including video surveillance and long distance communications, as well as mesh networks; and The Titan that supports heavy amp applications, such as ground radar, thermal imaging, or satellite uplink for mobile security solutions. The company also provides TeleMax, tEODor-Robust bomb disposal robot, ODIS-T2 for omni-directional inspection, and multi-mission next generation ODIS-T2 for ordinance disposal and inspection. In addition, the company offers unmanned aerial vehicles, such as Long Star and XTS UAV for aerial surveillance. Its products are used in various applications, including disaster recovery; physical security; border, pipeline, and perimeter; wireless communication nets; forward operating bases; event security; humanitarian services; and water desalination, purification, pumping, as well as in military and law enforcement, and industrial-security/safety organizations. The company was incorporated in 1987 and is based in Ashburn, Virginia.
